beer_description: A pale yellow lager that is very light in body yet with a good mouth feel from the flaked corn used during the brewing process.  A refreshing beer that is light on the palate that you can compare to your favorite premium domestic.  Pairs well with pretty much everything.

The nose is filled with complex notes of figs, fruitcake, port, licorice, cherry, raisin chocolate, black toffee, coffee and caramel, while it tastes deliciously thick and chewy, with great complexity showing notes of fruits, coffee-roastiness, molasses, licorice, and toffee. This beer is a meal!
Editor's note. The draught version is 9% abv, but also contained under this listing. Edit #2 The bottles are now 9% as well (from 7%)

Our Amber Ale is a full bodied, American-style amber with a rich copper color which comes from the roasted Amber and Munich malts. We use Cascade and Hallertauer Magnum hops to achieve the unique, fresh flavor and smooth finish that is long and complex on the palate. Originally brewed in 1989, this is our longest standing Signature beer. After all these years it?s still a brewery and regional favorite. A true beer drinker?s delight.

Das Meckatzer Weiss-Gold steht f?r au?ergew?hnlichen Biergenuss. Wir brauen es seit ?ber 100 Jahren nach ?berlieferter Rezeptur aus Allg?uer Gebirgswasser und wertvollen, nat?rlichen Zutaten der Region aus kontrolliert-integriertem Anbau. 1905 wurde seine Eintragung als erste Allg?uer Biermarke beim Kaiserlichen Patentamt in Berlin beantragt. ?ber den Ursprung des Meckatzer Weiss-Gold wissen wir nur wenig ? es ist ein geheimnisvoller Gl?cksfall der Braukunst. In handwerklicher Tradition (Zweimaischverfahren, Hei?w?rzefiltration, kalte Reifung) gebraut, stellt es einen eigenen Biertyp dar und ist daher keiner Biersorte unterzuordnen. Seine Komposition ist so harmonisch, dass man sie ? Analysen und Experimente best?tigen es ? nicht verbessern kann. Es gilt daher als das Allg?uer Sonntagsbier.

Up until the Second World War, dark beer was the predominant beer type in the Munich area. The hard water found in the region played a special role in producing this specialty. In his book ?Beer International?, the world-renowned English beer writer, Michael Jackson, accurately describes the Ayinger ?Altbairisch Dunkel? as: ?A good example of its kind. Impenetrably dark with a golden-brown gleam when held up to the light, and with a warm aroma and malty taste, while summoning up coffee taste sensations on going down. It is brewed from five types of malt (two of which are torrified dark), and it is only lightly hopped.? It is produced using the traditional double fermentation process.

Apparently made with spices?cinnamon, nutmeg and coriander?so you expect it to smell like mulled wine but in fact it has a very yeasty aroma. There are perfumed spicy notes there but it?s not what hits you first. Its colour is dark and it has a robust flavour with a heavy, hoppy, toasty, almost sour weight on the tongue.

Manchester Star was a brew discovered in an old recipe book (from about one hundred years ago). Manchester Star is a 7.3% ABV, dark ale, with chocolate, malty overtones and a warming finish made from 100% British ale malt, chocolate malt and Goldings hops. Manchester Star Ale is available in 100 Sainsbury?s stores nationwide (check which stores stock Manchester Star Ale near you).

Brewers of the world famous Saison DuPont, the DuPont Family Brewery lies in the pastoral Hainaut province of Belgium. Moinette Brune is the roasted malt version of the beloved Moinette Blonde. With gently sweet, almost fruity bouquet, full malt body and dry bracing finish, it's delicious before a meal and with roasted meats, chops and steaks.

Winter beer with a flamboyant color. Rich texture, very malty. Some hints of licorice and verbena that bring a lot of freshness. This beer has a good aging potential and will be even more enjoyable a few months after Christmas time.
Sour Swiss mashed classical strong bitter ale. Unfiltered, proudly handcrafted, top-fermented, bottle-conditioned ale. Limited edition.
California Ale Yeast, Cluster, Columbus & Northern Brewer Hops

Dieser Weissbier-Klassiker aus M?nchen steht in der langen Tradition bayerischer Weizen-Braukunst. Fr?her das alleinige Privileg der bayerischen Herz?ge, ist das Weissbier heute die bayerische und die typische M?nchner Bierspezialit?t. L?wenbr?u Weisse wird nach ?berlieferten Rezepten mit feinster, selbstgez?chteter Hefe gebraut und ?berzeugt durch seinen frischen, spritzigen Geschmack.
Eher trocken und malzbetont, s?ffig, mild, erinnert an Lakritze, kurze feine Bittere im Abgang // Eigenrezept , oberg?rig , 12% Stammw?rze , 4,0 % Alc.

Das St. Galler Landbier verdient seinen Namen zurecht. Schliesslich ist die helle, unterg?rige und Culinarium-zertifizierte Bierspezialit?t ein reines Naturprodukt aus der Region: Gebraut aus Gerstenmalz und Weizenmalz vom Gutsbetrieb Schloss Watt in M?rschwil, bestem Schweizer Hopfen aus Stammheim sowie Ribelmais aus dem Rheintal. Die behutsame G?rung und Lagerung vollendet das samtig-bierige Aroma des St. Galler Landbiers. Das erfrischende, leicht s?uerliche Aroma und die strahlend, goldgelbe Farbe mit dem Geruch nach frisch geerntetem Getreide und lichtgelbem Ribelmais verw?hnt den Geniesser.
Spritzig s?ffig, frisch im Gaumen: Weizenmalz und oberg?rige Hefe? Ein W?denswiler mit Charakter ? gebraut nach original bayrischem Rezept...

Vollmundig, leicht s?sslich, weich mit feinen Grasaromen, gew?rzt mit Hanfbl?ten.
Die Alternative zu klassisch gehopften Bieren.
Das Kristallklare W?denswiler: Schonend filtriert, herrlich spritzig und s?ffig, mit unerh?rter Eleganz ? Premium eben?

The traditional brand Schwaben Br?u represents Swabian beer specialities in a swing-top bottle. The typical ?plop? sound when you open the bottle is a sign of good taste.

"Das Schwarze" is a jet-black full-bodied beer that involves a complex brewing process and has an aromatic and tangy flavour.
